# Response mapping

See also: **`api-layer.mdc`**, **`zod-validation.mdc`**, **`frontend-feature-boundaries.mdc`**.

This is the frontend equivalent of backend **data exposure** control: components consume **UI models**, not raw API DTOs sprinkled through JSX.

## Core rule

**Never render API responses directly across the UI.**

1. **Parse** at the boundary (Zod in services or query `queryFn` when runtime safety matters).
2. **Map** DTOs → UI models in pure functions under `src/lib/<domain>/`.
3. **Components** import mappers or pre-mapped props — not `user.first_name` in ten files.

## Folder layout

| Layer            | Location example                          | Contains                          |
| ---------------- | ----------------------------------------- | --------------------------------- |
| API DTO / schema | `src/api/features/users/users.schema.ts`  | `userSchema`, `UserDto`           |
| Types (optional) | `src/api/features/users/users.types.ts`   | Re-exports / thin type aliases    |
| **UI mappers**   | `src/lib/users/mapUserToCard.ts`          | `mapUserToCard(dto): UserCardModel` |
| Display helpers  | `src/lib/users/formatUserLabel.ts`        | `formatUserLabel(dto): string`    |
| Components       | `src/pages/...`, `src/components/...`     | `UserCard` props = UI model       |

Naming: `map<Entity>To<Surface>`, `to<Surface>Model`, or `format<Entity><Field>` for single-field display.

## Bad vs good

```tsx
// Bad — backend rename breaks every callsite; leaks internal fields
<Card title={`${user.first_name} ${user.last_name}`} />
<span>{user.internal_account_status}</span>
```

```tsx
// Good — one mapper; component only knows UI shape
const card = mapUserToCard(user);
return <UserCard {...card} />;
```

```typescript
// src/lib/users/mapUserToCard.ts
import type { UserDto } from "@/api/features/users/users.schema";

export type UserCardModel = {
  displayName: string;
  subtitle: string;
  avatarUrl: string | null;
  statusLabel: string;
};

export function mapUserToCard(dto: UserDto): UserCardModel {
  return {
    displayName: `${dto.firstName} ${dto.lastName}`.trim(),
    subtitle: dto.email,
    avatarUrl: dto.avatarUrl ?? null,
    statusLabel: formatUserStatus(dto.status),
  };
}
```

Use **camelCase in UI models** even when the API uses `snake_case` — normalize in the mapper.

## Where mapping runs

| Approach              | When                                                |
| --------------------- | --------------------------------------------------- |
| Map in component      | Single use, trivial one-liner (still prefer helper) |
| Map in page container | Page-specific assembly from one query               |
| Map in `select`       | Narrow + transform in query hook for one consumer   |
| Map in lib helper     | **Default** — reused across pages/components        |

```typescript
// Optional: map inside query select when one hook feeds one UI
return useQuery({
  queryKey: userKey(id),
  queryFn: () => fetchUser(id),
  select: (dto) => mapUserToProfile(dto),
});
```

Prefer **lib mappers** when multiple surfaces consume the same entity.

## API evolution

When the backend changes field names or nesting:

- Update **schema + mapper** — not every component.
- Keep **deprecated** DTO fields out of UI models (do not pass through “just in case”).
- **Do not** expose internal ids, flags, or audit fields in card/list models unless the UI needs them.

## Lists & tables

```typescript
// src/lib/orders/mapOrderToRow.ts
export function mapOrdersToRows(dtos: OrderDto[]): OrderRowModel[] {
  return dtos.map(mapOrderToRow);
}
```

Table columns consume `OrderRowModel` — sorting labels and badges come from mapped fields, not raw enums from the wire format.

## Testing

Unit-test mappers in `src/test/lib/<domain>/` — pure functions, no mocks (`vitest-testing.mdc`). When API shape changes, mapper tests catch UI regressions early.

## Checklist

- [ ] JSX does not reference raw DTO field names (`snake_case`, internal keys) outside mappers.
- [ ] Reused entities have `map*To*` helpers under `src/lib/<domain>/`.
- [ ] UI models expose only what the surface needs — no whole DTO spread into props.
- [ ] Mapper tests cover renames, nulls, and enum → label mapping.
